<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName authority="section Talaromyces" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Aspergillaceae" genus="Talaromyces" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Talaromyces" order="Eurotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="section" section="Talaromyces">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Talaromyces section Talaromyces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="colony diam, 7 d (mm)">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Colony diam, 7 d (mm).</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">CYA 30-31; CYA 30 °C 28-30; CYA 37 °C 25-26; MEA 50-51; MEA 30 °C 57-60; OA 39-43; YES 42-43; CREA 13-14; CYAS No growth; DG18 13-15.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Colony characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
CYA 25 °C, 7 d: Colonies moderately deep, sulcate; margins entire; mycelium white and flesh (37); texture floccose; sporulation sparse; conidia 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">en masse</emphasis>
white; soluble pigments absent; exudates absent; reverse ochreous (44). MEA 25 °C, 7 d: Colonies moderately deep, plane; margins entire; mycelium white and primrose (66); texture floccose; sporulation sparse; conidia 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">en masse</emphasis>
white to greyish yellow-green (68); soluble pigments absent; exudates absent; reverse ochreous (44). YES 25 °C, 7 d: Colonies moderately deep, sulcate; margins entire; mycelium white; texture floccose; sporulation absent; soluble pigments absent; exudates absent; reverse ochreous (44). DG18 25 °C, 7 d: Colonies moderately deep, slightly raised at center, plane; margins entire; mycelium white; texture floccose; sporulation moderately dense; conidia 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">en masse</emphasis>
yellow-green (71); soluble pigments absent; exudates absent; reverse greyish yellow-green (68). OA 25 °C, 7 d: Colonies moderately deep, plane; margins entire; mycelium primrose (66); texture floccose; sporulation absent; soluble pigments absent; exudates absent; reverse primrose (66). Ascomata present. CREA 25 °C, 7 d: Moderate growth, acid production present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="micromorphology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Micromorphology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
Conidiophores monoverticillate and biverticillate; stipes smooth, 15-50 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
; metulae 3-5, divergent, 10-15 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
; phialides 4-6, flask-shaped, 9-13 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
; conidia smooth, subglobose to fusiform, 3-4(-5) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-3.5(-4.5) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Ascomata maturing after 2-3 wk of incubation on OA, yellow to orange, globose to subglobose, 400-550 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
; ascospores ellipsoidal, spiny, 3.5-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName authorityName="B. D. Sun, A. J. Chen, Houbraken &amp; Samson" authorityYear="2020" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Aspergillaceae" genus="Talaromyces" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Talaromyces brevis" order="Eurotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Talaromyces brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically and phylogenetically close to 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. liani" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="liani">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">T. liani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the latter produces larger ascospores measuring 4-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
and does not produce acid on CREA (except 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. liani" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="liani">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">T. liani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
CBS 118885 produces very weak acid) (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2014.08.001" author="Yilmaz, N" journalOrPublisher="Studies in Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" pagination="175 - 341" refId="B78" refString="Yilmaz, N, Visagie, CM, Houbraken, J, Frisvad, JC, Samson, RA, 2014. Polyphasic taxonomy of the genus Talaromyces. Studies in Mycology 78: 175 - 341, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2014.08.001" title="Polyphasic taxonomy of the genus Talaromyces." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2014.08.001" volume="78" year="2014">Yilmaz et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
Latin, 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="brevis" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, refers to its short conidiophores.
</paragraph>
